func Ignore() TestDeep Ignore operator is always true, whatever data is. It is useful when comparing a slice with Slice and wanting to ignore some indexes, for example (if you don&rsquo;t want to use SuperSliceOf). Or comparing a struct with SStruct and wanting to ignore some fields:
td.Cmp(t, got, td.SStruct( Person{ Name: &#34;John Doe&#34;, }, td.StructFields{ Age: td.Between(40, 45), Children: td.Ignore(), }), ) See also Ignore godoc.
Example Base example t := &amp;testing.T{} ok := td.Cmp(t, []int{1, 2, 3}, td.Slice([]int{}, td.ArrayEntries{ 0: 1, 1: td.Ignore(), // do not care about this entry 2: 3, })) fmt.Println(ok) // Output: // true
